# WhisperEngine Template-Based System Prompt Configuration
# Add this line to your .env or .env.{bot_name} file to enable template system

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# TEMPLATE-BASED SYSTEM PROMPT (NEW - November 2025)
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Enable template-based system prompt for ZERO per-message database overhead
# If this is set and file exists: Use template rendering (FAST - ~1ms)
# If not set or missing: Fallback to database CDL system (~60-120ms)

CHARACTER_SYSTEM_PROMPT_PATH=characters/system_prompts/elena.txt

# Benefits of template system:
# ✅ Zero per-message DB queries (vs 12+ for CDL)
# ✅ ~1ms template render (vs ~60-120ms DB overhead)  
# ✅ Git-trackable character personalities
# ✅ Easy debugging (read template file directly)
# ✅ Seamless fallback to database CDL if needed

# To test template system:
# 1. Uncomment the CHARACTER_SYSTEM_PROMPT_PATH line above
# 2. Restart bot: ./multi-bot.sh stop-bot elena && ./multi-bot.sh bot elena
# 3. Check logs for: "📄 TEMPLATE SYSTEM: Using template-based system prompt"
# 4. Test via HTTP: curl -X POST http://localhost:9091/api/chat -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"user_id":"test","message":"Hi Elena!"}'

# To create templates from database:
# python scripts/export_cdl_to_templates.py --character elena
# python scripts/export_cdl_to_templates.py --all

# Note: Dynamic data (user facts, memories, relationships) still uses PostgreSQL/Qdrant
# Only static character personality comes from template file
